RSA chat server

Arpit Jain
Anchal Khanna

The RSA chat server and client is written in C and uses TCP protocol.
The program supports  asynchronous sending and receiving of data.
The users exchange their public keys and send encrypted messages to each other which the receiver at each
end decrypts using his/her own private key.
The program also provides the functionality to break the private key of a user by brute force and determine the
original message.

Command line arguments:
Server : port number
client : port number and  hostname





